\fs24\insrsid2503371\charrsid12005122 Baptism is the entry into the Holy Church. It was commanded by our Savior, and has always been understood to be the entry of a believer into the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\b\fs24\insrsid2503371\charrsid12005122 Christian Life}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs24\insrsid2503371\charrsid12005122  in the Holy Church: \'93Go ye therefore, and teach all nations, baptizing them in the name of the F
ather, and of the Son, and of the Holy Ghost}{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\fs24\insrsid2503371\charrsid12005122 : Teaching them to observe all things whatsoever I have commanded you:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\fs24\insrsid2503371\charrsid12005122  and, lo, I am with you alway, even unto the end of the world. Amen}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\fs24\insrsid2503371 .\'94 }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\f1\fs24\insrsid2503371 
(St. Matthew 28:19-20).}{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af0\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\fs28\insrsid2503371  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs24\insrsid2503371\charrsid12005122 
