\f0\insrsid2503371\charrsid12005122 Baptism is not only the entry for the believer into the church; it also washes him clean of all sins prior to his holy baptism, no matter how grievous and frequent they were. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f0\cf0\revised\revauth1\revdttm-953451840\insrsid8272383\charrsid12005122 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s39\qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\pnrauth1\pnrdate-953451840\pnrnot1\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\cf0\revised\revauth1\revdttm-953451840\insrsid8272383\charrsid12005122 

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\insrsid2503371\charrsid12005122 Here he must remember the admonition the Lord gave to the paralytic, whom He healed of not only his physical infirmity, but of his sins also: \'93
Behold, thou art made whole: sin no more, lest a worse thing come unto thee\'94 }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2503371 (St. John 5:14).}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\insrsid2503371\charrsid12005122 
 We believe this because baptism is a complete rebirth, where the old man, with his sinful inclinations, dies, and is reborn in the Spirit. Our Lord said: \'93
Verily, verily, I say unto thee, Except a man be born of water and of the Spirit, he cannot enter into the kingdom of God.\'94 }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2503371 (John 3:5).}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f0\insrsid2503371\charrsid12005122  Therefore, baptism is necessary for our salvation.
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs20\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 
\fs24\insrsid2503371\charrsid12005122 
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\ql \li0\ri0\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\outlinelevel0\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1\afs28\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 
\b\f1\fs28\lang1033\langfe1033\kerning28\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2503371 {\*\bkmkstart _Toc452010836}The Gift of the Holy Spirit{\*\bkmkend _Toc452010836}
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\s38\qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs32\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs32\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\fs24\insrsid2503371\charrsid12005122 Chrismation is the imparting of the gift of the Holy Spirit unto the newly-baptized believer. Christians are \'93temples of the Holy Spirit\'94
, and this sacrament bestows the Holy Spirit upon them. The Christian must always remember St. Paul\rquote s admonition: \'93know ye not that your body is the temple of the Holy Ghost which is in you, which ye have of God, and ye are not your own?\'94 }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\fs24\insrsid2503371 (1 Cor 6:19). 
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\s39\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs24\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2503371 
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs20\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 
\fs24\insrsid2503371\charrsid12005122 After a person is baptized and chrismated, all his sins are remitted, and he is illumined with the grace and power of the H
oly Spirit to enable him to embark upon the life in Christ within the ark of the Holy Church. This is also the case for infants, who are also empowered to live a Christian life.  The grace of baptism, especially if it is nurtured by strong faith and piety
 in the household, will operate invisibly in such little ones, and strengthen them so that when they acquire reasoning powers, they will choose the Christian way of life. 
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\ql \li0\ri0\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\outlinelevel0\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1\afs28\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 
\b\f1\fs28\lang1033\langfe1033\kerning28\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2503371 {\*\bkmkstart _Toc452010837}Baptisms are public events}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3166428 {\*\bkmkend _Toc452010837}.}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2503371 
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs20\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 
\fs24\insrsid2503371\charrsid12005122 Baptisms should be public, bef
ore the entire local parish, so that all the Christians can pray for the ones to be illumined, and may listen again to the vows that are made, remembering their own vows. It is good for every Christian to examine himself during this time, to see whether h
e be \'93in Christ\'94 or not, that is, whether he has kept the vows of his baptism. 
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\ql \li0\ri0\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\outlinelevel0\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1\afs28\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 
\b\f1\fs28\lang1033\langfe1033\kerning28\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2503371 {\*\bkmkstart _Toc452010838}I believe in one baptism{\*\bkmkend _Toc452010838}
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs20\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 
\fs24\insrsid2503371\charrsid12005122 \'93I believe in one baptism\'94 is said by every Christian every day when he recites the Symbol of Faith (the Creed). Since the
re is only one church, there is only one baptism. Nothing outside the church, even if it resembles Christian baptism, is true baptism.  This is why those desiring to become Orthodox Christians who come from another belief, even one that has a baptismal ri
t
e, should be baptized. Certain innovators have begun to accept people into Orthodoxy by chrismation only, and espouse an ecumenical rhetoric which accepts their baptismal rite outside the church as fully Christian in every way. They have made up a service
 
for this, as there is no separate service for chrismation - it is part of the baptismal rite. Any chrismation service written in our modern days and intended for those who desire to enter Holy Orthodoxy is an innovation, and was unknown by the Holy Father
s of the Church.  
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\ql \li0\ri0\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\outlinelevel0\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1\afs28\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 
\b\f1\fs28\lang1033\langfe1033\kerning28\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2503371 {\*\bkmkstart _Toc452010839}Chrismation and special circumstances{\*\bkmkend _Toc452010839}
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs20\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 
\fs24\insrsid2503371\charrsid12005122 Chrismation, since it is the imparting of the gift of the Holy Spirit, may be repeated under extreme conditions. We believe that the Holy Spirit flees from an Orthodox Chris
tian when he falls into apostasy, or idol worship. When he repents and comes back to the Holy Church, he is often, according to the discretion of the bishop, accepted back by chrismation, which again imparts the gift of the Holy Spirit back to him. There 
is a special service in our Trebnic (\'93Book of Needs\'94
, which the priest uses for special services such as marriage, burial, baptism, various blessings, etc.) for the chrismation of formerly apostate Orthodox. This service is certainly not the one used by cer
tain Orthodox when they chrismate people they incorrectly say \'93are already baptized\'94
, as it is a very compunctionate service, and assumes that the person being chrismated is an apostate Orthodox, desiring to repent and enter back into the life in the church.
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\ql \li0\ri0\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\outlinelevel0\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1\afs28\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 
\b\f1\fs28\lang1033\langfe1033\kerning28\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2503371 {\*\bkmkstart _Toc452010840}A Proper Form and Belief{\*\bkmkend _Toc452010840} 
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs20\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2503371 

\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\s2\ql \li0\ri0\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\outlinelevel1\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af1\afs24\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\i\f1\fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {
\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2503371 {\*\bkmkstart _Toc452010841}The Proper Form{\*\bkmkend _Toc452010841}
