\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs20\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 
\fs24\insrsid2503371\charrsid12005122 From the day of our baptism, we embark on a life or death struggle in the \'93arena\'94
, as some of the Fathers have called the world in which we live. Our only goal must be the salvation of our souls, as this is the purpose of 
our life on the earth. The Holy Church teaches us everything we need to know, and here we find the Most Holy Trinity, and work out the salvation of our souls, with \'93fear and trembling\'94. 
\par 
\par In any struggle, there are victories and setbacks, moments of great 
joy, and times of overwhelming sadness. So it is with the Christian life. We must pray, and keep the fasts, and attend the Holy Services, considering them to be more important that our jobs, and as necessary as the air we breath. We must try to learn God
\rquote s Holy Commandments, and follow them. When we fall down, we always have repentance, and Holy Confession. We have the Holy Mysteries, Jesus Christ\rquote 
s very Body and Blood to nourish us, as we struggle to acquire the mind of Christ and be worthy of the baptismal garment we have been given. May God preserve us and help us in this holy endeavor, by the prayers of His most pure mother, and all the Saints!

\par 
